  "body": "### Overview\r\n_Provide a simple overview of what you wish to see added. Please include:_\r\nSo far, when we use Brownie, using python we have 2 options:\r\n1. use pipx\r\n2. use pip\r\nwhy dont give the opportunity to use brownie into a container or a full venv?\r\n\r\n_What you are trying to do_\r\n I am trying to use brownie on a full virtual env\r\n\r\n_Why Brownie's current functionality is inadequate to address your goal_\r\n- Just wondering if is possible and works fine. Reading you docu it is not an option\r\n- IMO have the possibility to create smarcontracts on a virtual env is more \"clean\" and secure\r\n\r\n### Specification\r\n_Describe the syntax and semantics of how you would like to see this feature implemented. The more detailed the better!_\r\n\r\nI just wondering if brownie works 100% if someone wants install and run brownie console on a python venv \r\nFor example:\r\n1) create a virtual env using python3 -m venv myvenv\r\n2) run myvenv\r\n3) install brownie into myvenv\r\n\r\n### Dependencies\r\nInclude links to any open issues that must be resolved before this feature can be implemented.\r\nN/A\r\n",
